288
00:22:48,111 --> 00:22:50,739
Bell-bottoms bleached.

289
00:22:50,814 --> 00:22:52,805
Shoes all shined up.

290
00:22:52,882 --> 00:22:55,146
Now alls we need
is an organ grinder.

291
00:22:55,218 --> 00:22:58,745
Welcome to Bayonne, New Jersey.
Pimple on God's ass.

292
00:22:58,822 --> 00:23:01,484
Chief Sunday, we never met,
but I served with you on the Hoist.

293
00:23:03,193 --> 00:23:06,094
U.S.S. Hoist.
I 'spect I 'member you now.

294
00:23:07,163 --> 00:23:09,097
So what's for chow, cookie?

295
00:23:09,165 --> 00:23:12,134
I wouldn't know, Chief.
I'm reporting for diving school.

296
00:23:12,202 --> 00:23:14,693
Oh, yeah, that's right.

297
00:23:14,771 --> 00:23:17,797
They say you wrote over 100 letters
requesting admission to this school.

298
00:23:17,874 --> 00:23:19,808
You got you
some grit in you, huh?

299
00:23:19,876 --> 00:23:24,643
- Yes, sir.
- Well, it's gonna be a hot one today.

300
00:23:30,553 --> 00:23:33,852
Sure hope you're better
than the last cook.
That man's food could kill your dog.

301
00:23:36,259 --> 00:23:38,819
Chief.

302
00:23:41,497 --> 00:23:43,431
[ Indistinct Chattering ]

303
00:23:50,874 --> 00:23:54,037
[ Chattering Continues ]

304
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:56,044
- Thank you.
- All righteous.

305
00:23:56,112 --> 00:23:58,046
There you go.

306
00:24:00,083 --> 00:24:02,017
[Trainees Shouting]

307
00:24:20,970 --> 00:24:23,700
Had yourself
anything to drink today?

308
00:24:23,773 --> 00:24:26,071
No, sir, Chief.

309
00:24:26,142 --> 00:24:28,804
What say we go on into town
and get us a nice cold one?

310
00:24:28,878 --> 00:24:31,676
I can't do that, Chief.
I haven't reported for duty.

311
00:24:31,748 --> 00:24:35,684
I tell you what.
I'll buy you a tall one over there.

312
00:24:35,752 --> 00:24:40,246
A bus ticket too, so you can go back
to whatever burg you sprang from.

313
00:24:40,323 --> 00:24:43,053
What do you say?

314
00:24:43,126 --> 00:24:45,287
Sir, I am a Navy man.

315
00:24:45,361 --> 00:24:47,625
Where I come from,
there are no oceans.

316
00:24:47,697 --> 00:24:50,825
Only dirt farms
and ornery mules.

317
00:24:52,635 --> 00:24:57,197
And no self-respecting Navy man
makes a living driving mules.

318
00:25:02,745 --> 00:25:05,373
Sir.

319
00:25:13,856 --> 00:25:15,790
You know what the Chinese say,
cookie?

320
00:25:18,728 --> 00:25:21,253
Beware what you wish for.

321
00:25:24,033 --> 00:25:26,934
- [Man Chanting]
I stole a pie! I stole a pie!
- Let him in.

322
00:25:28,838 --> 00:25:31,932
- [Chanting Continues]
I stole a pie! I stole a pie!
- [Metal Clanking]

323
00:25:32,008 --> 00:25:35,705
I stole a pie!
I stole a pie!

324
00:25:35,778 --> 00:25:39,111
I stole a pie!
I stole a pie!

325
00:25:39,182 --> 00:25:42,151
- [Chanting Continues]
- [ Dog Whimpering ]

326
00:25:42,218 --> 00:25:46,279
Get in there.
Go on. Hoist away.

327
00:25:46,356 --> 00:25:48,950
[Whimpering Continues]

328
00:25:49,025 --> 00:25:51,255
[Men Laughing]

329
00:25:55,164 --> 00:25:57,098
[ Laughter Continues ]

330
00:26:02,672 --> 00:26:05,368
[Stuttering]
Do-Do-Do-Don't stare at him.

331
00:26:05,441 --> 00:26:07,966
- Who is he?
- The commanding officer,

332
00:26:08,044 --> 00:26:11,810
b-b-but everyone calls him
M-M-Mr. Pappy.

333
00:26:11,881 --> 00:26:13,781
- He's a war hero.
- Here.

334
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:16,216
They, they were gonna make him
an admiral up in D. C....

335
00:26:16,285 --> 00:26:20,654
'f-f-fore they,
they found out he's got more,
more screws loose than a Studebaker.

336
00:26:20,723 --> 00:26:26,252
So they sent him here.
Better salute him or you'll be
spending your first night in the brig.

337
00:26:28,664 --> 00:26:30,598
[Chanting Continues]
I stole a pie!

338
00:26:33,269 --> 00:26:36,170
[ Stuttering Continues ]
Come on. I'll show you the barracks.

339
00:26:36,239 --> 00:26:39,174
[Men Chattering, Indistinct]

340
00:26:41,611 --> 00:26:44,478
[ Chattering Stops ]

341
00:27:01,631 --> 00:27:03,292
[ Man ]
Attention on deck!

342
00:27:11,941 --> 00:27:15,035
Gentlemen, in 1948,

343
00:27:15,111 --> 00:27:18,410
President Harry S. Truman
had the courage and forward-thinking
and enlightenment...

344
00:27:18,481 --> 00:27:21,075
to desegregate
the United States military.

345
00:27:21,150 --> 00:27:26,315
Now I want y'all to welcome the Bayonne
Diving School's first colored trainee,

346
00:27:26,389 --> 00:27:29,187
Bosun's Mate
Second Class Carl Brashear.

347
00:27:33,963 --> 00:27:37,228
I don't hear anyone welcomin'
Bosun's Mate Brashear.

348
00:27:42,638 --> 00:27:46,472
Master Chief,
no disrespect to the president,

349
00:27:47,543 --> 00:27:49,534
but I don't bunk with niggers.

350
00:29:03,252 --> 00:29:07,120
- Aren't you gonna go too?
- N-N-N-No.

351
00:29:08,391 --> 00:29:10,757
I-I-I-I'm from Wisconsin.

352
00:29:12,528 --> 00:29:14,462
Never been there.

353
00:29:17,667 --> 00:29:20,761
[ Radio: Static, Tuning ]

354
00:29:20,836 --> 00:29:23,304
[ Announcer] Haily gets a fast ball
low and inside for strike three,

355
00:29:23,372 --> 00:29:25,772
and Jackie Robinson strikes out.

356
00:29:25,841 --> 00:29:30,141
[Radio Announcer Continues,
Indistinct]

357
00:29:32,081 --> 00:29:36,279
And the score as we had it
on the top of the seventh:
Brooklyn, one, Milwaukee, one.

358
00:29:42,458 --> 00:29:44,119
[ Gasping ]

359
00:29:44,193 --> 00:29:46,957
Rise and shine, cookie.
Time for trainin'.

360
00:29:47,029 --> 00:29:49,361
[ Spits, Gasps ]

361
00:29:52,435 --> 00:29:55,734
- [ Coughing ]
- Are you familiar with
the principle of Boyle's Law?

362
00:29:55,805 --> 00:29:57,534
The what?

363
00:29:57,607 --> 00:30:00,303
I didn't hear your answer.

364
00:30:01,410 --> 00:30:03,556
[Coughing Continues]

365
00:30:03,689 --> 00:30:05,919
Come on, cookie.
Get up.

366
00:30:05,991 --> 00:30:09,154
- [ Coughing Continues ]
- Boyle's Law states that,
at a constant temperature,

367
00:30:09,228 --> 00:30:14,165
the volume of a confined ideal gas
varies inversely with its pressure!

368
00:30:14,233 --> 00:30:17,828
- Now why is this law
important in divin'?
- I don't know, Chief!

369
00:30:17,903 --> 00:30:21,168
You ain't never gonna know,
'cause you're just some dumb
dirt nigger from Podunk!

370
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:25,506
I know you.
Your sweet smell hung in every bunk
and goddamn shack I ever lived in.

371
00:30:25,578 --> 00:30:29,139
Your nigger face stared at me
every time we had to leave...

372
00:30:29,215 --> 00:30:31,547
'cause your daddy
could farm it cheaper than mine.

373
00:30:31,617 --> 00:30:35,109
Mine drank himself into a $7 casket,
but that ain't gonna happen to me...

374
00:30:35,187 --> 00:30:37,382
because I'm a Master Diver!

375
00:30:37,456 --> 00:30:41,859
Maybe you'll remember that next time
you imply we got anything in common!

376
00:30:41,927 --> 00:30:43,895
- You read me, cookie?
- [ Coughing, Gasping ]

377
00:30:46,365 --> 00:30:48,697
- What?
- Get your goddamn Wisconsin ass...

378
00:30:48,768 --> 00:30:51,498
back to bed, Snowhill!

379
00:31:21,434 --> 00:31:25,564
The men you are watching
are going to be Navy divers.

380
00:31:25,638 --> 00:31:29,005
You bottom suckers are not fit
to observe them.

381
00:31:29,074 --> 00:31:31,201
Avert your eyes!

382
00:31:31,277 --> 00:31:34,110
My name is Master Chief
Billy Sunday.

383
00:31:34,180 --> 00:31:37,445
There's a preacher by the same
name cleaned up Chicago...

384
00:31:37,516 --> 00:31:41,247
of all the whorin' spics, drunken wops
and motherfuckin' niggers...

385
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:45,620
that was makin' that place unfit
for decent white folks to live.

386
00:31:45,691 --> 00:31:48,854
The only difference between me
and that old preacher...

387
00:31:48,928 --> 00:31:52,420
is that he worked for God
and I am God!

388
00:31:52,498 --> 00:31:55,467
[Gulls Squawking]

389
00:31:55,534 --> 00:31:59,698
Now, why don't the first ten of
you Girl Scouts step forward?

390
00:31:59,772 --> 00:32:02,240
Come on!
Drop your dicks! Let's go!

391
00:32:04,343 --> 00:32:06,538
Three quarters of you
standing here today...

392
00:32:06,612 --> 00:32:09,172
will fail
to become Navy divers.

393
00:32:09,248 --> 00:32:12,217
Three from the first row,
step forward. Step forward!

394
00:32:16,155 --> 00:32:18,316
Of those unfortunates
that do pass,

395
00:32:18,390 --> 00:32:20,950
only three of you will live
to reach retirement...

396
00:32:21,026 --> 00:32:24,120
'cause divin'is the most
dangerous job in the Navy.

397
00:32:25,698 --> 00:32:28,132
So who wants to quit?

398
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:30,225
Say it now,
who wants to quit?

399
00:32:30,302 --> 00:32:33,635
You got somethin' to offer,
huh?

400
00:32:36,775 --> 00:32:41,974
Who wants to save me the sweat
of training your sorry ass?

401
00:32:42,047 --> 00:32:44,777
You? You?

402
00:32:44,850 --> 00:32:46,784
Cookie?

403
00:32:50,923 --> 00:32:53,858
You?

404
00:32:53,926 --> 00:32:56,793
You gonna look me
in the eye, son, huh?

405
00:32:57,997 --> 00:33:00,693
What are you,
some kind of broke-dick Popeye?

406
00:33:02,368 --> 00:33:05,531
Huh? Let me guess.

407
00:33:05,604 --> 00:33:07,663
You were captain
of the swim team, weren't you?

408
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:11,676
You and your girlfriend used
to practice the breast stroke!

409
00:33:12,745 --> 00:33:16,306
[ Stuttering ]

410
00:33:16,382 --> 00:33:18,373
Say it
like you got a pair!

411
00:33:18,450 --> 00:33:21,283
- My w-w-w-wife.
- Oh, that's right.

412
00:33:21,353 --> 00:33:24,845
It's in your record.
You knocked her up sophomore year.

413
00:33:24,924 --> 00:33:28,416
Well, maybe you can bring
the little w-w-w-woman down one night...

414
00:33:28,494 --> 00:33:32,089
and all the boys can practice
the b-b-b-breast stroke.

415
00:33:34,567 --> 00:33:38,799
I heard you were a hell of a swimmer,
Snowhill. State champ?

416
00:33:38,871 --> 00:33:41,738
Y-Yes, y-yes,
M-Master Chief.

417
00:33:45,578 --> 00:33:48,206
Snowhill,
please step forward.

418
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:50,214
Come on.

419
00:33:51,283 --> 00:33:53,217
About face.

420
00:33:57,089 --> 00:33:59,751
- [ Grunts ]
- You let go before I relieve you,

421
00:33:59,825 --> 00:34:03,056
you fail my course right now,
got it, swim champ?

422
00:34:03,128 --> 00:34:05,688
[ Grunts ]

423
00:34:10,336 --> 00:34:14,705
Swimmin' don't got dick shit
to do with deep-sea divin'.

424
00:34:14,773 --> 00:34:16,798
If Johnny fuckin' Weismuller
were in the soup...

425
00:34:16,875 --> 00:34:19,435
wearin' a 200-pound
Mark Five divin' rig,

426
00:34:19,511 --> 00:34:21,445
he couldn't swim
to fuck Esther Williams...

427
00:34:21,513 --> 00:34:24,209
if she was three feet
in front of him buck naked.

428
00:34:24,283 --> 00:34:26,877
The only way to survive
is to trust each other,

429
00:34:26,952 --> 00:34:29,079
'cause underwater all you got
is the man next to you.

430
00:34:29,154 --> 00:34:32,248
And that is why the only men
that get through my course...

431
00:34:32,324 --> 00:34:34,383
are the very, very best.

432
00:34:34,460 --> 00:34:36,394
Now get out of my sight.

433
00:34:37,963 --> 00:34:40,193
- [ Trainee ] Boy, I don't know.
- [ Chattering Continues ]

434
00:34:47,673 --> 00:34:49,732
Permission to relieve
the man below, Master Chief.

435
00:34:49,808 --> 00:34:53,141
What are you, cookie,
some kind of goddamn hero?

436
00:34:53,212 --> 00:34:56,079
I got no room in my class for heroes
or stutterin' swim champs...

437
00:34:56,148 --> 00:34:58,742
with a wife and kids
to worry about, do you read me?

438
00:34:58,817 --> 00:35:02,378
If you wanna flunk me, flunk me, but
don't punish him for being decent to me.

439
00:35:02,454 --> 00:35:06,322
I don't have to flunk you.
You're gonna do that all on your own.
He had half a chance.

440
00:35:06,392 --> 00:35:09,054
He still does.
Permission to relieve him.

441
00:35:09,128 --> 00:35:12,757
Claims he can hold his breath over four
minutes. Hell, it ain't even been two.

442
00:35:12,831 --> 00:35:16,733
- [ Gasping ]
- I believe Gunner's Mate
Snowhill's a liar!

443
00:35:16,802 --> 00:35:19,965
Now we're men of honor, ain't we,
cookie? We don't abide liars.

444
00:35:20,039 --> 00:35:22,633
You're out of my program,
Snowhill.

445
00:35:22,708 --> 00:35:25,336
Bosun's Mate Brashear,
you have the barracks to yourself.

446
00:35:25,411 --> 00:35:28,175
[Snowhill Gasping]

447
00:35:28,247 --> 00:35:30,647
Damn!
[ Panting ]

448
00:35:30,716 --> 00:35:32,650
The Navy diver
is not a fighting man.

449
00:35:32,718 --> 00:35:35,983
He is a salvage expert.
If it's lost underwater, he finds it.

450
00:35:36,055 --> 00:35:39,286
If it's sunk, he brings it up.
If it's in the way, he moves it.

451
00:35:39,358 --> 00:35:42,657
If he's lucky, he'll die young
200 feet beneath the waves...

452
00:35:42,728 --> 00:35:44,992
for that is the closest he will
ever get to being a hero.

453
00:35:45,064 --> 00:35:48,465
Hell, I don't know why anybody'd
want to be a Navy diver.

454
00:35:48,534 --> 00:35:51,935
Good flange work, Rourke.
Almost there.

455
00:35:52,004 --> 00:35:53,938
Thank you, Master Chief.

456
00:36:01,814 --> 00:36:03,916
[Man]
Machinist's Mate Rourke, 91.

457
00:36:03,916 --> 00:36:04,211
[Man]
Machinist's Mate Rourke, 91.

458
00:36:04,283 --> 00:36:08,515
Bosun's Mate Brashear, 37.

459
00:36:08,587 --> 00:36:12,250
- If you fail the next test,
you're out of the program.
- Yes, sir.

460
00:36:12,324 --> 00:36:16,556
There are seats of learning beyond
the walls and control of this camp.

461
00:36:22,768 --> 00:36:26,226
Ladies,
this is weekend liberty.

462
00:36:26,305 --> 00:36:31,641
Anyone's ass
that ain't back here on time
will have to answer to me personally.

463
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:35,271
And remember, ladies, one-night stands
may be over by mornin',

464
00:36:35,347 --> 00:36:38,043
but syp hilis lasts
a lifetime.

465
00:36:38,117 --> 00:36:41,450
- Dismissed!
- [ Cheering, Hooting ]

466
00:36:44,923 --> 00:36:46,857
[ Tires Screech, Horn Honks ]

467
00:36:46,925 --> 00:36:51,362
[Man In Car]
Watch out.

468
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:53,660
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

469
00:36:56,101 --> 00:36:58,035
- Have fun, baby.
- [Man]Flowers!

470
00:36:58,103 --> 00:37:01,698
Flowers! Hey, how about some flowers
for your young lady, huh?

471
00:37:17,923 --> 00:37:20,016
What's the hitch?

472
00:37:24,029 --> 00:37:27,021
- You're the one who called.
- Yes, ma'am.

473
00:37:27,099 --> 00:37:31,001
[ Sighs ]
I told you. We're a public library,

474
00:37:31,069 --> 00:37:33,765
not a tutoring service.

475
00:37:33,839 --> 00:37:38,469
Now, if you don't mind,
there is a Mr. Biddle at home.

476
00:37:38,544 --> 00:37:41,035
In fact, he's probably
brought flowers.

477
00:37:41,113 --> 00:37:43,138
[Wheels Squeak]

478
00:37:55,327 --> 00:37:58,854
Have a wonderful weekend.
And lock up, would you?

479
00:37:58,931 --> 00:38:02,765
- Uh-huh.
- And be sure to kick him out.

480
00:38:03,902 --> 00:38:08,171
- Hello.
- We're closed.

481
00:38:08,304 --> 00:38:12,934
Not for three minutes.
You studying on nursin'?

482
00:38:13,009 --> 00:38:16,137
A person doesn't "study on"
anything, Bosun's Mate.

483
00:38:19,048 --> 00:38:22,711
You know your rates and ranks. Did you
get that from one of these books?

484
00:38:25,321 --> 00:38:28,256
Look, I'm not here
to flirt with you.

485
00:38:28,324 --> 00:38:31,122
I'm in diving school
across the river.

486
00:38:31,194 --> 00:38:34,960
I'm not just good at it.
I was born for it.

487
00:38:35,031 --> 00:38:38,091
But the joke is, I'm gonna wash out
if I don't pass my next exam.

488
00:38:38,167 --> 00:38:40,601
What was the last grade
you completed in school?

489
00:38:40,670 --> 00:38:43,662
- Seventh.
- I can't help you.

490
00:38:43,740 --> 00:38:46,937
- Why not?
- Because it took me four years
of working at places like this...

491
00:38:47,010 --> 00:38:48,944
to get through med school.

492
00:38:49,012 --> 00:38:52,504
Now I have six weeks to study for
my exam. I pass, I become an intern,

493
00:38:52,582 --> 00:38:54,743
and maybe someday
become a doctor.

494
00:38:54,817 --> 00:38:58,776
You're too far behind,
and I don't have the time.

495
00:38:58,855 --> 00:39:01,983
Okay. Go on.
Walk around reading to yourself.

496
00:39:02,058 --> 00:39:04,686
- Don't give me another thought.
Just go on.
- Don't you get it?

497
00:39:04,761 --> 00:39:08,094
Whether I help you or not doesn't
matter. You're gonna fail anyway.

498
00:39:08,164 --> 00:39:12,658
I won't. I can't.

499
00:39:15,104 --> 00:39:17,163
Why do you want this
so badly?

500
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:19,538
Because they said
I couldn't have it.

501
00:39:39,829 --> 00:39:42,662
I may know
a professor at City--

502
00:40:16,799 --> 00:40:19,461
[Book Pages Turning]

503
00:40:28,911 --> 00:40:34,611
Boyle's Law describes
the behavior of gases undervarying
amounts of atmospheric pressure.

504
00:40:34,684 --> 00:40:38,518
It states that if a diver
holds his breath at 100 feet,

505
00:40:38,588 --> 00:40:40,852
continues holding while rising
to ten feet,

506
00:40:40,923 --> 00:40:44,222
then the gases in his lungs
increase four times.

507
00:40:44,293 --> 00:40:46,227
Now why is this important
to a diver?

508
00:40:46,295 --> 00:40:48,627
Forget to exhale on the way up,
and your lungs explode.

509
00:40:52,168 --> 00:40:56,161
I can work with you,
but my time is precious.

510
00:40:56,239 --> 00:40:59,868
So the first time you go out
drinking and fighting...

511
00:40:59,942 --> 00:41:02,911
and leave me waiting here,
our arrangement ends.

512
00:41:04,447 --> 00:41:07,814
- [Door Closes]
- [ Chuckles ]

513
00:41:07,884 --> 00:41:10,284
- [Bell Dings]
- [Woman]Good morning.

514
00:41:19,829 --> 00:41:25,096
I, um... have to open up.

515
00:41:25,168 --> 00:41:27,830
Now are you gonna tell me your
name, or is it still a secret?

516
00:41:27,904 --> 00:41:30,839
My name is Jo.
[ Chuckles ]

517
00:41:32,308 --> 00:41:34,936
My father always wanted
a boy.

518
00:41:36,078 --> 00:41:38,638
He was in the Navy too.

519
00:41:38,714 --> 00:41:43,083
- Is he still active?
- I haven't seen him since I was nine.

520
00:41:45,588 --> 00:41:47,522
[Bell Dinging]

521
00:41:57,333 --> 00:41:59,767
Mm-mm, mm-mm.
Like this.

522
00:42:03,673 --> 00:42:06,733
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

523
00:42:06,809 --> 00:42:08,936
- Good night.
- Good night.

524
00:42:10,613 --> 00:42:13,104
- [ Chattering Continues ]
- [Man]
Fire Controlman Mellegrano, 91.

525
00:42:13,182 --> 00:42:16,982
Mate DuBoyce, 85.
Engineman Crofoot, 69.

526
00:42:17,053 --> 00:42:21,149
Bosun's Mate
Carl Brashear,

527
00:42:21,224 --> 00:42:23,158
76.

528
00:42:23,226 --> 00:42:26,218
[Low Chattering]

529
00:42:28,231 --> 00:42:32,565
- [ Instructor Chattering ]
- [ Sighs ]

530
00:42:32,768 --> 00:42:34,998
[Man]Boots, cookie,
tear yourselves away, ladies.

531
00:42:35,071 --> 00:42:38,268
You're next in the water. You're gonna
go down to the training vessel,

532
00:42:38,341 --> 00:42:42,402
patch ahole so we canpump her full
of air and raise her to the surface.

533
00:42:42,478 --> 00:42:45,811
Then we're gonna sink her
and do it again.

534
00:42:45,881 --> 00:42:50,716
[Man]Because underwater,
all you've got is the man next to you!

535
00:42:50,786 --> 00:42:53,152
Chief, what the hell's
goin' on down there?

536
00:42:53,222 --> 00:42:55,747
That boy stays down there any longer,
he's gonna start gettin' mail.

537
00:43:04,767 --> 00:43:07,531
Isert, come on.
Finish torching that hole.

538
00:43:07,603 --> 00:43:09,571
I'm tryin',
but this thing's real awkward.

539
00:43:11,207 --> 00:43:13,607
- How's it look?
- [ Sighs ] Looks like hell.

540
00:43:13,676 --> 00:43:16,110
Green Diver, this is
Master Chief Sunday.

541
00:43:16,178 --> 00:43:20,512
You have three minutes
to get your patch hot and hung
before the next team comes down.

542
00:43:20,583 --> 00:43:22,710
[Sunday]Nowcome on, Isert!
Move your raggedy ass!

543
00:43:22,785 --> 00:43:24,753
- RedDiver?
- Yes, Master Chief.

544
00:43:24,820 --> 00:43:27,948
God damn it, Rourke, I've had girlfriends
that could weld faster than that.

545
00:43:28,024 --> 00:43:30,584
- Now move him along.
- [ Laughs ]

546
00:43:30,660 --> 00:43:34,221
- Come on, Isert. Now hang your patch.
- Yeah, okay, Rourke. I'm trying.

547
00:43:36,198 --> 00:43:38,928
[ Grunting ]

548
00:43:41,337 --> 00:43:44,704
- Hey, Isert, you feel that?
- Do I feel what?

549
00:43:46,008 --> 00:43:48,476
- What the hell?
- [ Grunting ]

550
00:43:48,544 --> 00:43:52,446
[Rourke]
Topside, this wreck is moving!

551
00:43:52,515 --> 00:43:54,710
She's limping, Chief!
We're sliding down!

552
00:43:54,784 --> 00:43:57,548
Somebody tell me
what just happened?

553
00:43:57,620 --> 00:43:59,884
- [Rourke] Top side!
- Get it! Grab that hose!

554
00:44:14,670 --> 00:44:18,606
- Red Diver, what's your situation?
- The ship just dropped 50 feet.

555
00:44:18,674 --> 00:44:22,166
- We landed on something.
- Better bring those boys home
till we figure this out.

556
00:44:22,244 --> 00:44:26,408
- Square yourselves away.
You're coming home.
- Negative on the come home.

557
00:44:26,482 --> 00:44:28,848
- Isert's got his air hose tangled.
- [ Grunts ]

558
00:44:28,918 --> 00:44:32,547
- My air hose is stuck!
- Fouled. Now get it unfouled.

559
00:44:33,656 --> 00:44:36,352
[Grunting Continues]

560
00:44:36,425 --> 00:44:38,791
Rourke, what's wrong?
Why are we movin'?

561
00:44:38,861 --> 00:44:41,329
- We slipped partway
down the channel bank.
- Rourke!

562
00:44:45,167 --> 00:44:49,103
- This wreck is live!
- You get this off!

563
00:44:49,171 --> 00:44:51,662
- I'm gonna have to change out
his lifeline and air hose.
- [Sunday] Listen, Rourke.

564
00:44:51,741 --> 00:44:54,972
He's your buddy.
You follow his line back,
unfoul it and get him out of there.

565
00:44:55,044 --> 00:44:57,535
I'm trying, but it's just too tight.
Send down a line!

566
00:44:59,415 --> 00:45:01,508
- [ Isert Yells ]
- [ Rourke ] Help!

567
00:45:01,584 --> 00:45:03,711
- I need help down here.
- Help's on the way.

568
00:45:03,786 --> 00:45:06,186
- I'm ready, Master Chief.
- Dennis, undress him.

569
00:45:06,255 --> 00:45:10,783
- You can't go down there.
- Better not be talking to me.
I won't haveyour familiar tone.

570
00:45:12,027 --> 00:45:15,519
You can't dive that deep.
I'm ready. Let me go.

571
00:45:23,563 --> 00:45:26,430
Master Chief, it looks
like the ship slid down...

572
00:45:26,499 --> 00:45:29,730
on some discharge pipes
coming from that factory.

573
00:45:29,802 --> 00:45:33,898
They give out, and this whole ship's
going right to the bottom.

574
00:45:33,973 --> 00:45:37,636
[Sunday] You don't worry about
that boat.Just get that hose to Rourke.

575
00:45:44,283 --> 00:45:46,683
- [Crash]
- [ Rourke ] For God's sake!

576
00:45:46,753 --> 00:45:50,211
- [Sunday]
What the hell was that, cookie?
- Look!

577
00:45:50,289 --> 00:45:52,484
The ship's weight is crushing
those pipes, Chief.

578
00:45:52,558 --> 00:45:55,356
Gotta get him on a fresh hose
and out of here fast!

579
00:45:55,428 --> 00:45:59,865
Topside, Blue Diver's here.
He's gota fresh line.

580
00:45:59,932 --> 00:46:03,197
All right, lsert.
Rourke's gonna change you out, and
you're gonna be walking out of there.

581
00:46:03,269 --> 00:46:06,932
- Okay.
- That boy's got five minutes
of air if he don't panic.

582
00:46:07,006 --> 00:46:09,372
You screw up the change out,
and that boy's dead, read me?

583
00:46:09,442 --> 00:46:12,843
- Yes, Master Chief.
- Isert, we're not gonna be able
to talk for a few minutes.

584
00:46:12,912 --> 00:46:15,676
I want you to think of your favorite
song, and I want you tosing it.

585
00:46:15,748 --> 00:46:19,582
- I don't know any songs.
- You got to slow your respiration.
Breathe easy.

586
00:46:19,652 --> 00:46:23,452
- Just breathe easy.
- Please. I wasn't made for this.

587
00:46:23,523 --> 00:46:27,220
I want to go home now!
I want to go home now!

588
00:46:27,293 --> 00:46:29,227
Would you let me
come home now?

589
00:46:29,295 --> 00:46:33,595
I want to quit!l want to quit!
I really want to quit!

590
00:46:33,666 --> 00:46:36,601
- I want to quit!
- Change him out now!

591
00:46:39,806 --> 00:46:42,969
- She's movin', Chief!
- Come on, Rourke! I got him!

592
00:46:43,042 --> 00:46:46,603
[Isert Grunting]

593
00:46:48,047 --> 00:46:51,574
- [ Air Hissing ]
- Topside, Isert's off air.

594
00:46:55,054 --> 00:46:57,545
- What's going on down there?
- She's gonna roll over!

595
00:46:57,623 --> 00:47:01,150
I 'spect so. You stay down there,
and you change that boy out, hear me?

596
00:47:02,862 --> 00:47:06,263
- [ Isert ] Rourke!
- [ Rourke ] I'm out of here!

597
00:47:06,332 --> 00:47:08,266
I gotta get out of here!
She's going down!

598
00:47:08,334 --> 00:47:10,427
- Rourke, come back here!
- Rourke!

599
00:47:10,503 --> 00:47:13,097
- Rourke, get back here!
- I ain't dying!

600
00:47:13,172 --> 00:47:15,106
- [Carl] Rourke!
- [Rourke] I'm out of here.

601
00:47:15,174 --> 00:47:18,143
Don't leave!
Carl, don't leave me!

602
00:47:18,211 --> 00:47:22,204
I need my air hose!
I can't breathe, Carl!

603
00:47:22,281 --> 00:47:24,215
I'm getting dizzy!

604
00:47:31,757 --> 00:47:33,918
[ Both Yelling ]

605
00:47:43,936 --> 00:47:46,302
[ Both Grunting ]

606
00:47:50,610 --> 00:47:53,010
I can't breathe.

607
00:47:53,079 --> 00:47:54,637
[ Gasping ]

608
00:48:07,426 --> 00:48:11,055
- Topside, he's blacking out!
- Goddamn it, hook him up!

609
00:48:13,132 --> 00:48:16,568
- I got it!
- [ Gasping Continues ]

610
00:48:23,743 --> 00:48:26,405
[Isert Breathing]

611
00:48:35,922 --> 00:48:39,653
- [Carl] We're coming home, Chief.
- Never doubted it.

612
00:48:55,408 --> 00:48:58,605
[ Labored Breathing ]

613
00:49:09,588 --> 00:49:12,716
Machinist Mate First Class Rourke,
front and center!

614
00:49:25,237 --> 00:49:28,035
"The president of the
United States of America...

615
00:49:28,107 --> 00:49:31,702
takes great pleasure inpresenting
the Navy and Marine Corps
Medal of Heroism...

616
00:49:31,777 --> 00:49:34,871
to Machinist Mate First Class
Dylan Rourke,

617
00:49:34,947 --> 00:49:38,610
whereby Petty Officer Rourke
on the 22nd of September...

618
00:49:38,684 --> 00:49:40,914
of the year 1952,

619
00:49:40,987 --> 00:49:42,921
with apparent disregard
for his own life,

620
00:49:42,989 --> 00:49:47,323
did, at Bayonne, New Jersey,
save the life of
Petty Officer Timothy Douglas Isert."

621
00:50:09,081 --> 00:50:11,015
Post.

622
00:50:21,761 --> 00:50:23,991
Class 0252 dismissed.

623
00:50:46,952 --> 00:50:48,886
[Phone Ringing]

624
00:50:56,629 --> 00:50:58,563
[Ringing Continues]

625
00:50:58,631 --> 00:51:02,089
- [Woman] Carl?
- Hey, I got your telegram.

626
00:51:02,168 --> 00:51:05,296
No, no, no. I got the wire.
How's Daddy doing?

627
00:51:05,371 --> 00:51:07,805
Is he up and around again?

628
00:51:21,153 --> 00:51:23,849
- [ Hooting, Chattering ]
- Yeah! Yeah!

629
00:51:26,725 --> 00:51:28,659
[ Crying ]

630
00:51:48,347 --> 00:51:50,281
[ Sailors Chattering ]

631
00:52:22,515 --> 00:52:25,882
[Jo ]
Hello? Carl? Is that you?

632
00:52:25,951 --> 00:52:29,011
Hey,Jo.
Hey, it's me.

633
00:52:29,088 --> 00:52:31,249
Where are you?
Are you okay?

634
00:52:31,323 --> 00:52:34,554
[ Crying ]
No, I'm okay. I'm okay.

635
00:52:34,627 --> 00:52:39,587
Uh, listen, uh,

636
00:52:39,665 --> 00:52:41,599
c-could you meet me?

637
00:52:41,667 --> 00:52:43,692
[ Tires Screech ]

638
00:52:43,769 --> 00:52:46,897
- Goddamn it!
- Okay. I'll stay here.

639
00:52:46,972 --> 00:52:52,638
Damn it! The miserable son of a bitch
in there drinkin' on my anniversary!

640
00:53:03,055 --> 00:53:05,785
You're the one, aren'tyou?

641
00:53:09,528 --> 00:53:11,758
Well, I'm Gwen... Sunday.

642
00:53:21,640 --> 00:53:23,665
Sorry to hear that.

643
00:53:32,484 --> 00:53:35,453
You know he's gonna
kick you out of the Navy.

644
00:53:40,526 --> 00:53:43,017
He's gonna kick you out
of diving.

645
00:53:49,401 --> 00:53:52,666
So what
you gonna do about it?

646
00:53:52,738 --> 00:53:55,969
You just gonna let him run you over,
just like you do everyone else?

647
00:54:01,614 --> 00:54:04,310
You know, he's in there
right now.

648
00:54:06,485 --> 00:54:09,010
- [ Chattering ]
- [Gwen]He wanted a party,

649
00:54:09,088 --> 00:54:11,420
let's give him one.

650
00:54:16,418 --> 00:54:18,215
-##[Country]
- [ Stuttering ] She told me...

651
00:54:18,287 --> 00:54:21,017
it was okay
to dance with a girl.

652
00:54:21,090 --> 00:54:24,548
[ Chattering Continues ]

653
00:54:28,597 --> 00:54:31,191
[Gwen]
Oh, llove this song!

654
00:54:31,266 --> 00:54:34,963
[ Vocalizing ]

655
00:54:35,037 --> 00:54:38,404
- [Gwen Humming]
-##[Continues, Indistinct]

656
00:54:40,576 --> 00:54:44,706
Donny, be a dear lad
and get us two scotches.

657
00:54:44,780 --> 00:54:49,444
- We're out.
- Lucky for us, you got
a whole bar full of bourbon.

658
00:55:01,130 --> 00:55:03,155
What the hell are you doing,
bringin' him in here?

659
00:55:07,970 --> 00:55:12,066
- Get out.
- Well, I'll be goddamned.

660
00:55:12,141 --> 00:55:15,008
It's prom night
here at the Moor Bar.

661
00:55:15,077 --> 00:55:18,513
You boys, you have
a drink on me. Go ahead.

662
00:55:22,985 --> 00:55:25,215
Hell, I don't know
who classes up the joint more--

663
00:55:25,287 --> 00:55:29,053
the fetching young lady
in the fur stole or cookie here.

664
00:55:29,124 --> 00:55:34,152
So what'd you two kids come here
to do anyway? Dance?

665
00:55:34,229 --> 00:55:38,029
Why not take a turn?
It's a free country, mostly.

666
00:55:38,100 --> 00:55:40,568
You made a big mistake,
walking in here, cookie.

667
00:55:40,636 --> 00:55:44,902
- Oh, it's my fault.
- It's all your fault.

668
00:55:44,973 --> 00:55:48,932
Spoiled little rich girl gets her kicks
draggin' stray men in here.

669
00:55:49,011 --> 00:55:53,948
Thinks we're just
a bunch of sweaty rednecks
she can shake up for the fun of it.

670
00:55:54,016 --> 00:55:58,976
Hey, Donny, bea dearlad
and bring the lady a fresh soldier.

671
00:56:00,422 --> 00:56:02,583
Think you deserve a beer,
don't you?

672
00:56:02,658 --> 00:56:05,320
Fraternizing among Navy men.

673
00:56:05,394 --> 00:56:07,919
Think you're
as good as they are?

674
00:56:07,996 --> 00:56:09,930
How 'bout me, cookie?
You better than me?

675
00:56:09,998 --> 00:56:12,728
- You're damn right, I am.
- Mm-hmm.

676
00:56:18,540 --> 00:56:20,565
You see this pipe?

677
00:56:20,642 --> 00:56:25,341
General MacArthur himself
smoked this pipe.

678
00:56:25,414 --> 00:56:27,473
I served with him
in Leyte Gulf.

679
00:56:27,549 --> 00:56:29,744
Biggest naval battle
in history.

680
00:56:29,818 --> 00:56:33,185
Kamikaze ripped into this escort
carrier, name of Saint Lo.

681
00:56:33,255 --> 00:56:38,784
She went down on a shallow reef,
trapping me and six boys
in the fire room.

682
00:56:38,860 --> 00:56:41,658
- Only one way out.
- Flood the compartment and swim up.

683
00:56:41,730 --> 00:56:45,860
Five decks, cookie.
Five fuckin' decks.

684
00:56:45,934 --> 00:56:48,164
Locked bulk heads,
dead bodies everywhere.

