00:56:48,237 --> 00:56:52,765
You got to have your balls
screwed on tight for that swim.

686
00:56:52,841 --> 00:56:56,834
We still had intercom. Old MacArthur
himself came over that squawk box,

687
00:56:56,912 --> 00:56:58,846
"Sunday,
you cocky son of a bitch,

688
00:56:58,914 --> 00:57:03,146
I bet you can't hold your breath for
four minutes and swim out of there."

689
00:57:03,218 --> 00:57:05,846
Know what I said back?

690
00:57:05,921 --> 00:57:10,119
" No, Mac, I can't, but
I'll bet you your cob pipe...

691
00:57:10,192 --> 00:57:13,525
I can hold it for five, 'cause that's
what it's gonna take, motherfucker."

692
00:57:13,595 --> 00:57:16,530
- C-C-C-Carl, this ain't worth--
- Get your hands off me.

693
00:57:16,598 --> 00:57:20,295
There's six men still breathin' today,
'cause I led 'em out of that fire room.

694
00:57:20,369 --> 00:57:23,827
And now just 'cause you pulled little
Isert's white little fuckin' ass...

695
00:57:23,905 --> 00:57:27,534
out of some row boat
sunk in a mud puddle,
you think you're better than me?

696
00:57:27,609 --> 00:57:29,839
Well, let's just see.

697
00:57:37,219 --> 00:57:40,711
What's your bet, cookie?

698
00:57:40,789 --> 00:57:44,555
- Put Snowhill back in diving.
- What do you owe him?

699
00:57:44,626 --> 00:57:47,026
- Nothing. You owe him.
- Oh, yeah?

700
00:57:47,095 --> 00:57:51,930
Fine. If I win, you ship out,
tonight. Deal?

701
00:57:55,570 --> 00:57:58,130
Deal.

702
00:57:58,206 --> 00:58:01,975
- [Man]Show him, Master Chief!
- [Hooting, Chattering]

703
00:58:02,809 --> 00:58:04,902
Will you be my tender?

704
00:58:04,978 --> 00:58:07,412
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

705
00:58:07,481 --> 00:58:10,416
[Cheering, Shouting]

706
00:58:10,484 --> 00:58:13,681
Come on, baby!

707
00:58:13,753 --> 00:58:16,688
[ Cheering Continues ]

708
00:58:33,773 --> 00:58:35,764
Let's go, baby!

709
00:58:37,611 --> 00:58:40,136
Come on, now.

710
00:58:44,551 --> 00:58:47,042
Come on, Sunday!

711
00:58:50,790 --> 00:58:54,954
- Go!
- Come on, Master ChiefSunday!

712
00:58:55,028 --> 00:58:57,792
[Cheering Continues]

713
00:59:10,243 --> 00:59:13,269
One minute,
fifteen seconds.

714
00:59:16,449 --> 00:59:18,883
[ Whistling ]

715
00:59:18,952 --> 00:59:21,386
[ Cheering Continues ]

716
00:59:38,838 --> 00:59:42,296
[Sailor]
Two minutes, twenty-five seconds.

717
00:59:42,375 --> 00:59:45,833
Hey, it's another
ten bucks right here!

718
00:59:48,548 --> 00:59:50,516
Sunday, do it!

719
00:59:56,523 --> 01:00:00,118
Three minutes, ten seconds!

720
01:00:12,305 --> 01:00:15,035
Come on.

721
01:00:15,108 --> 01:00:17,975
- Four minutes!
- Four minutes! Four!

722
01:00:19,412 --> 01:00:21,346
- Stop it!
- No.

723
01:00:21,414 --> 01:00:24,212
- Chief.
- Stop it! Stop!

724
01:00:25,652 --> 01:00:28,246
[ Sighs ]

725
01:00:37,163 --> 01:00:41,759
- Rourke, stop it!
- [ Indistinct Shouting ]

726
01:00:46,773 --> 01:00:52,405
Carl, you-you okay?
Carl?

727
01:00:52,479 --> 01:00:55,778
- Carl?
- Chief Sunday, you all right?

728
01:00:55,849 --> 01:00:58,249
- Hold it!
- You all right, Chief Sunday?

729
01:00:58,318 --> 01:01:00,786
- [ Gasping ] I'm okay.
- Hold him up.

730
01:01:00,854 --> 01:01:03,288
- I got it.
- Hold it!

731
01:01:03,356 --> 01:01:06,120
- He's all right.
- Come on!

732
01:01:06,192 --> 01:01:08,126
Come on, hold him up!

733
01:01:08,194 --> 01:01:11,357
- [Horn Honks, Car Crashes]
- Let's go!

734
01:01:11,431 --> 01:01:14,923
She tried to drive off the pier
like a crazy woman!

735
01:01:15,001 --> 01:01:18,095
- Get her outta the car!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

736
01:01:18,171 --> 01:01:22,369
- Hey, hey.
- You know,
today's my wedding anniversary.

737
01:01:22,442 --> 01:01:24,740
- [ Crowd Chattering ]
- You're gonna be all right.

738
01:01:24,811 --> 01:01:28,269
Come on, move, move.
Come on, babe.

739
01:01:28,348 --> 01:01:33,149
- [ Crying ] No, not you, Billy!
- Come on, baby, come on.

740
01:01:33,219 --> 01:01:35,153
Bastard!

741
01:01:35,221 --> 01:01:38,384
- [ Continues Crying ]
- Come on, baby. Come on.

742
01:01:38,458 --> 01:01:40,892
[Sunday Coughs, Mutters]

743
01:01:40,960 --> 01:01:45,124
- Come on, baby, let's go home.
- Yeah?

744
01:01:45,198 --> 01:01:48,099
- Come on.
- Yeah?

745
01:01:48,168 --> 01:01:51,103
[Sailor]
Go on home now. Nothin' to see here.

746
01:01:52,706 --> 01:01:54,640
Jo.

747
01:01:54,708 --> 01:01:56,642
Jo!

748
01:01:59,012 --> 01:02:03,176
I can't do this, Carl.
I can't live this life again.

749
01:02:03,249 --> 01:02:07,083
I pulled my father out of
more Navy bars than I care to count.

750
01:02:07,153 --> 01:02:10,611
-Jo, you don't know
what happened tonight.
- Oh, but I do.

751
01:02:14,961 --> 01:02:16,952
I passed my finals.

752
01:02:17,030 --> 01:02:20,363
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry,Jo.

753
01:02:20,433 --> 01:02:23,891
The point is, I'm gonna be
starting my internship at Bellevue.

754
01:02:23,970 --> 01:02:27,167
- It's gonna be crazy hours.
I won't have time to see you.
- I made a mistake.

755
01:02:27,240 --> 01:02:29,902
- It won't happen again.
- Oh, yes, it will.

756
01:02:29,976 --> 01:02:34,913
You wanted to fight that man.
You were just waiting for the moment.

757
01:02:34,981 --> 01:02:39,918
Don't you see...
I'm not like you?

758
01:02:39,986 --> 01:02:43,581
[ Sobbing ]
The things I want--

759
01:02:45,959 --> 01:02:50,225
The things I want
are smaller.

760
01:02:50,296 --> 01:02:53,026
If I just work hard
and keep my head down--

761
01:02:53,099 --> 01:02:56,364
Your whole life
will pass you by.

762
01:03:03,443 --> 01:03:06,879
Carl, most of what's
in those diving books...

763
01:03:06,946 --> 01:03:09,881
you know better than,
than me.

764
01:03:09,949 --> 01:03:13,612
You don't need me anymore.
You don't need anyone.

765
01:03:13,686 --> 01:03:16,177
I love you.

766
01:03:33,973 --> 01:03:35,907
[Engine Starts]

767
01:03:38,678 --> 01:03:40,612
Jo!

768
01:03:40,680 --> 01:03:42,841
Jo! Jo!

769
01:03:42,916 --> 01:03:46,511
- Jo! Hey,Jo!
- What?

770
01:03:46,586 --> 01:03:49,749
Jo! Marry me!

771
01:03:49,823 --> 01:03:52,291
He wants to know
if you'll marry him.

772
01:04:23,656 --> 01:04:24,891
- [Knocking]
- [Pappy]Come in.

773
01:04:24,891 --> 01:04:25,823
- [Knocking]
- [Pappy]Come in.

774
01:04:25,892 --> 01:04:29,055
Watch the door, Chief.
Try not to touch anything.

775
01:04:40,840 --> 01:04:43,434
[Glass Clattering]

776
01:05:04,898 --> 01:05:08,265
Did you know
that ordinary house dust...

777
01:05:08,334 --> 01:05:11,497
is composed primarily
of human skin?

778
01:05:13,273 --> 01:05:15,332
No, sir,
I didn't know that.

779
01:05:15,408 --> 01:05:20,345
[ Chuckles ] Makes you think twice
about who you invite into your home.

780
01:05:24,484 --> 01:05:26,418
[ Sniffs ]

781
01:05:31,691 --> 01:05:34,182
Two table spoons
of machine oil...

782
01:05:34,260 --> 01:05:37,058
can contaminate...

783
01:05:37,130 --> 01:05:41,965
an entire ship's
fresh water supply.

784
01:05:44,137 --> 01:05:47,573
Some things just don't mix.

785
01:05:49,709 --> 01:05:52,542
Do they, Chief?

786
01:05:55,248 --> 01:05:57,808
He's gonna pass.

787
01:05:57,884 --> 01:06:01,411
Yesterday, he scored
a 94 onhis final.

788
01:06:01,487 --> 01:06:03,819
Sir, he don't have to be
that fast tomorrow.

789
01:06:03,890 --> 01:06:06,654
All he's got to do
is complete the exercise.

790
01:06:11,698 --> 01:06:14,394
Billy...

791
01:06:19,272 --> 01:06:23,072
there may come a day when a colored
diver graduates from this school,

792
01:06:23,142 --> 01:06:26,873
but it won't be tomorrow
or as long as I'm here.

793
01:06:28,948 --> 01:06:31,439
You agree with me,
of course.

794
01:06:32,986 --> 01:06:37,116
- Don't you, Chief?
- Yes, sir.

795
01:06:41,327 --> 01:06:45,170
[Door Opens, Closes]

796
01:06:48,740 --> 01:06:51,675
##[Radio: Country]

797
01:07:13,231 --> 01:07:15,825
Baseball season's
over, cookie.

798
01:07:17,569 --> 01:07:20,538
I figured Rourke.
I never even let myself think--

799
01:07:20,605 --> 01:07:24,063
- Why not?
- 'Cause I saw your last dive.

800
01:07:26,144 --> 01:07:30,080
You want to know what I am?
I'm the sorry son a bitch put here...

801
01:07:30,148 --> 01:07:34,244
to get through your thick fucking skull
that some things do not change.

802
01:07:34,319 --> 01:07:36,947
- I deserve to pass.
- Since when does deserving
mean anything?

803
01:07:37,022 --> 01:07:38,956
They ain't gonna have
a colored diver.

804
01:07:39,024 --> 01:07:42,585
'Cause no matter what you do, in their
eyes, you'll never be as good as them.

805
01:07:42,660 --> 01:07:44,958
- So, deserving or otherwise,
you're failing.
- No, you are.

806
01:07:45,030 --> 01:07:47,055
You think
I owe you somethin'?

807
01:07:47,132 --> 01:07:49,999
I don't owe you
a goddamn fucking thing.

808
01:07:50,068 --> 01:07:53,629
You or anybody else. You got fucked,
cookie. Happens to the best of us.

809
01:07:53,705 --> 01:07:56,538
You were right, Chief.
Youand I have nothing in common.

810
01:07:56,608 --> 01:08:00,510
I may be some dirt dumb nigger
from Podunk, but at least
I'm making something of myself.

811
01:08:00,578 --> 01:08:03,979
You, you're the same hateful,
little man you started out as.

812
01:08:04,049 --> 01:08:06,347
Without diving,
you're nothing...

813
01:08:06,418 --> 01:08:09,854
but a lost, broke-down son of a bitch
who used to be something.

814
01:08:26,604 --> 01:08:28,868
Hey!

815
01:08:28,940 --> 01:08:31,773
What did he say to you
to make you try so hard?

816
01:08:31,843 --> 01:08:34,175
" Be the best."

817
01:08:34,245 --> 01:08:36,338
Well, you are.

818
01:08:38,149 --> 01:08:42,085
Just don't show up tomorrow.
Pappy ain't gonna let you pass.

819
01:08:47,325 --> 01:08:49,657
What about you, Chief?

820
01:08:53,898 --> 01:08:57,629
[ Sunday] Today will decide
which of you will become Navy Divers.

821
01:08:57,702 --> 01:09:02,162
The object of this test is to correctly
assemble this flange underwater.

822
01:09:02,240 --> 01:09:05,073
The pieces required for assembly
await you on the river bottom.

823
01:09:05,143 --> 01:09:09,512
Once you have located your project
flange, you will call for your tools.

824
01:09:09,581 --> 01:09:12,175
They will be lowered to you.

825
01:09:12,250 --> 01:09:16,710
You will be timed on your effort
and will accrue points
for a speedy completion.

826
01:09:16,788 --> 01:09:20,349
However, we'll keep pumping
air down to you for as long
as you can stand the cold.

827
01:09:20,425 --> 01:09:24,486
So take your time
and get it right.

828
01:09:51,289 --> 01:09:53,951
[Sunday]
If you do not complete the flange,

829
01:09:54,025 --> 01:09:57,483
you have just wasted
six months of your lives.

830
01:10:08,406 --> 01:10:12,740
Divers, square yourselves away
and approach the rail.

831
01:10:53,785 --> 01:10:56,913
Topside, I have located
my work light.

832
01:11:17,508 --> 01:11:19,442
Topside, Blue Diver.

833
01:11:19,510 --> 01:11:22,707
I have located my project
and am requesting my toolbag.

834
01:11:22,780 --> 01:11:27,114
Topside, this is Red Diver.
I have located my project flange.

835
01:11:27,185 --> 01:11:31,281
- Requesting my tool bag.
- Tenders, lower your tool bags.

836
01:11:55,079 --> 01:11:58,139
Topside, Blue Diver.
I'm still waiting on my tool bag.

837
01:12:31,282 --> 01:12:34,581
Blue Diver, your tool bag
is on the river bottom.

838
01:12:51,202 --> 01:12:55,696
Chief, start the project time
on all divers.

839
01:13:20,498 --> 01:13:24,059
Machinist Mate Rourke,
one hour, thirty-seven minutes.

840
01:13:24,135 --> 01:13:26,899
Perfect assembly.

841
01:13:48,893 --> 01:13:52,954
Survey or Second Class Yarmouth,
two hours, nineteen minutes.

842
01:13:53,030 --> 01:13:55,658
Perfect assembly.

843
01:14:01,406 --> 01:14:04,068
[ Panting ]

844
01:14:12,517 --> 01:14:14,781
I never thought
I'd live to see it.

845
01:14:14,852 --> 01:14:18,720
Four hours and nine minutes. Better
late than never, Engineman Crofoot.

846
01:14:18,790 --> 01:14:21,987
Perfect assembly.
How's the water down there?

847
01:14:22,059 --> 01:14:24,994
It's colder than
a well digger's ass, Master Chief.

848
01:14:25,062 --> 01:14:27,225
Take it inside.

849
01:14:59,857 --> 01:15:01,882
[Phone Ringing]

850
01:15:01,959 --> 01:15:05,622
[ Man On Phone, Indistinct ]

851
01:15:05,696 --> 01:15:07,960
What do you mean,
he's still not up?

852
01:15:34,459 --> 01:15:37,223
[ Shuddering ]

853
01:16:00,751 --> 01:16:03,549
Excuse me.

854
01:16:11,829 --> 01:16:14,423
[Phone Ringing]

855
01:16:19,103 --> 01:16:21,094
Dive station,
Master Diver speaking.

856
01:16:21,172 --> 01:16:24,107
Chief Sunday, we have every cook
and shine boy in this camp...

857
01:16:24,175 --> 01:16:26,473
thinking they'll be next
to try a stunt like this.

858
01:16:26,544 --> 01:16:28,478
So you listen up.

859
01:16:28,546 --> 01:16:31,037
Don't bring him up
till he stops moving.

860
01:16:31,115 --> 01:16:33,049
He's near dead now, sir.

861
01:16:33,117 --> 01:16:35,312
Not till he stops moving,
Chief.

862
01:16:42,627 --> 01:16:44,595
Give it up, cookie.

863
01:16:44,662 --> 01:16:47,392
You go into shock down there,
you might not wake up.

864
01:16:47,465 --> 01:16:50,332
Come on, now.
This ain't worth dyin' for.

865
01:16:50,401 --> 01:16:52,596
[ Shuddering ]
M-My name is...

866
01:16:52,670 --> 01:16:56,436
Bosun's Mate Second Class...

867
01:16:56,507 --> 01:16:58,771
C-C-Carl Brashear.

868
01:17:00,978 --> 01:17:03,173
I am a Navy Diver.

869
01:17:28,506 --> 01:17:32,636
Bring him up.
Bring him up!

870
01:17:32,710 --> 01:17:34,644
- I got him.
- We're bringing him home.

871
01:17:34,712 --> 01:17:38,170
Sailor,
disregard that order!

872
01:17:39,750 --> 01:17:42,583
Sailor! Sailor!

873
01:17:42,653 --> 01:17:47,556
Chief Sunday,
effective immediately,

874
01:17:47,625 --> 01:17:51,026
I am relieving you
of your duties!

875
01:17:51,095 --> 01:17:53,529
Do you hear me, Chief?

876
01:17:56,434 --> 01:17:58,834
Hold the line.
Hold that line.

877
01:18:06,611 --> 01:18:09,205
[Metal Clanging]

878
01:18:21,759 --> 01:18:25,388
Come on, Brashear.
You're almost there.

879
01:18:25,463 --> 01:18:28,796
Just a few more steps.
Come on, we'll help you.

880
01:18:31,602 --> 01:18:34,264
A little more.
[ Grunting ]

881
01:18:34,338 --> 01:18:36,272
That's it.

882
01:18:42,413 --> 01:18:45,075
[ Air Escaping ]

883
01:18:45,149 --> 01:18:47,310
Open it up.

884
01:19:05,836 --> 01:19:08,100
Bosun's Mate Second Class
Carl Brashear,

885
01:19:08,172 --> 01:19:10,606
nine hours,
thirty-one minutes.

886
01:19:10,675 --> 01:19:13,303
Perfect assembly.

887
01:19:20,518 --> 01:19:22,452
Get him inside.

888
01:19:23,621 --> 01:19:25,555
[Men Shouting Encouragement]

889
01:19:25,623 --> 01:19:28,251
Help him out!
[Shouting Continues]

890
01:19:40,137 --> 01:19:42,935
Carl, d-d-did y-y-you h-hear--

891
01:19:43,007 --> 01:19:45,737
-Slow down, Snowhill.
-They put me back in the diving program.

892
01:19:45,810 --> 01:19:48,335
- I start training next week.
- Congratulations.

893
01:19:48,412 --> 01:19:51,279
Thanks, Carl.

894
01:19:51,349 --> 01:19:54,580
Hey, I almost forgot.
Y-Y-You hear about Sunday?

895
01:19:54,652 --> 01:19:59,453
- No.
- M-Mr. Pappy blew a gasket
when the son of a bitch passed you.

896
01:19:59,523 --> 01:20:02,754
He b-busted him down ashred
and shipped him out.

897
01:20:02,827 --> 01:20:05,261
I guess that fucker
got his in the end, huh?

898
01:20:06,931 --> 01:20:09,331
I guess he did.

899
01:20:09,400 --> 01:20:11,664
[ Panting ]

900
01:20:14,805 --> 01:20:16,830
Guess he did.

901
01:20:59,316 --> 01:21:03,685
[ Man Singing Country]
Will you still say

902
01:21:03,754 --> 01:21:06,882
 I love you, dear-- 

903
01:21:10,060 --> 01:21:13,496
 [ Swing ]

904
01:21:22,006 --> 01:21:25,100
From the gentleman.

905
01:21:25,176 --> 01:21:27,201

906
01:21:27,278 --> 01:21:30,111

907
01:21:30,181 --> 01:21:32,547

908
01:21:32,616 --> 01:21:34,550

909
01:21:34,618 --> 01:21:37,178

910
01:21:37,254 --> 01:21:40,189
- You hate champagne.

911
01:21:40,257 --> 01:21:43,420
- You got a diving assignment.

912
01:21:43,494 --> 01:21:45,985
Brooklyn Navy Yard.
Stand by diver.

913
01:21:46,063 --> 01:21:49,032
Brooklyn? Brooklyn!

914
01:21:49,099 --> 01:21:52,796
Oh, baby, we can have dinner
like an old married couple.

915
01:21:52,870 --> 01:21:55,532
Oh, well, baby,
I didn't take the job.

916
01:21:55,606 --> 01:21:58,769
We've been waiting three years
for that slot to open up.

917
01:21:58,843 --> 01:22:01,311
Jo, I don't move up
in rank unless I dive.

918
01:22:01,378 --> 01:22:04,779
And I'll never make Master as a stand by
diver. I'll find something else.

919
01:22:11,555 --> 01:22:15,082
- I'm three months late.
- Late for what?

920
01:22:21,265 --> 01:22:24,894
You're gonna have--
A real... baby?

921
01:22:24,969 --> 01:22:28,735
We're gonna have a baby!
We're gonna have a real baby!

922
01:22:28,806 --> 01:22:30,933
- [ Chuckles ]
