Come Friday,
that Captain Hanks--

1165
01:44:23,931 --> 01:44:27,298
he's gonna convene a medical review
board, and he's gonna retire you.

1166
01:44:29,570 --> 01:44:32,539
- He said I had four weeks.
- He lied, cookie.

1167
01:44:32,607 --> 01:44:36,202
He don't give a shit how many
one-legged push-ups you can do.

1168
01:44:36,277 --> 01:44:39,440
He'd trade you and me and every
other old sea dog in the Navy...

1169
01:44:39,513 --> 01:44:42,107
for one glass-eyed
electronics technician.

1170
01:44:42,183 --> 01:44:44,208
The man's gonna retire
your ass.

1171
01:44:44,285 --> 01:44:46,276
I got my leg back.
I ain't done yet.

1172
01:44:46,354 --> 01:44:49,881
You got a stump on a wooden stick and
no goddamn chance of beating Hanks, son.

1173
01:44:55,263 --> 01:44:58,061
All I ever wanted to do
was to make Master Diver.

1174
01:44:58,132 --> 01:45:01,568
All I ever wanted to do
was stay one.

1175
01:45:01,636 --> 01:45:07,006
You want to beat Hanks, you've got to
go around him, right to the top.

1176
01:45:07,074 --> 01:45:10,066
- Washington.
- Mm-hmm.

1177
01:45:10,144 --> 01:45:13,238
- Chief of Naval Personnel.
- That's right.

1178
01:45:13,314 --> 01:45:17,375
And they don't like cocky pencil-pushers
like Hanks any more than we do.

1179
01:45:20,321 --> 01:45:22,881
I might be able
to pull a few strings.

1180
01:45:29,630 --> 01:45:31,723
Why are you doing this,
Sunday?

1181
01:45:35,169 --> 01:45:37,103
Piss people off.

1182
01:45:37,171 --> 01:45:41,540
Chief Decker, you are the Chief Master
at Arms of this hospital, are you not?

1183
01:45:41,609 --> 01:45:44,237
Yes, sir.

1184
01:45:44,312 --> 01:45:49,249
Then why is it you don't know
where Chief Brashear is?

1185
01:45:49,317 --> 01:45:51,877
He shouldn't be
too hard to spot.

1186
01:45:51,953 --> 01:45:55,480
He is the only Negro
diver in the Navy,

1187
01:45:55,556 --> 01:45:57,547
and he's got one leg.

1188
01:45:57,625 --> 01:46:01,959
It seems that the chief
has transferred, sir.

1189
01:46:02,029 --> 01:46:04,361
To where?

1190
01:46:04,432 --> 01:46:07,924
- On whose orders?
- He signed his own orders, sir.

1191
01:46:08,002 --> 01:46:11,733
- Call the Shore Patrol.
- Relax, Cap. We just wanna talk.

1192
01:46:13,341 --> 01:46:17,300
Wait, wait, wait, wait. You know
where Chief Brashear is. Where?

1193
01:46:19,981 --> 01:46:23,417
I see. Fine.
Chief Brashear is AWOL.

1194
01:46:23,484 --> 01:46:25,645
I want him found
and arrested now.

1195
01:46:25,720 --> 01:46:29,781
- You ain't gonna find him.
- What doyou want from me, Chief?

1196
01:46:29,857 --> 01:46:32,758
Four weeks to train him, then
a full readiness evaluation...

1197
01:46:32,827 --> 01:46:35,557
and reinstatement hearing with
the Chief of Naval Personnel.

1198
01:46:35,629 --> 01:46:37,358
[ Chuckles ]
The chief of--

1199
01:46:37,431 --> 01:46:39,797
- Yes, sir.
- At the Navy yard in Washington?

1200
01:46:39,867 --> 01:46:41,732
- That's right.
- Forget it.

1201
01:46:44,472 --> 01:46:46,940
[ Clears Throat ]

1202
01:46:47,008 --> 01:46:51,342
- [Reporters Shouting]
- Will the diver be allowed
to be reinstated?

1203
01:46:51,412 --> 01:46:56,281
Seems Chief Brashear
losing his leg for his country
sort of makes him a hero, sir.

1204
01:46:56,350 --> 01:46:58,284
Fine.

1205
01:47:02,890 --> 01:47:07,190
I will grant you your hearing
on one condition, hmm?

1206
01:47:07,261 --> 01:47:11,197
When he fails, you retire.

1207
01:47:11,265 --> 01:47:14,962
- He ain't gonna fail.
- Hmm.

1208
01:47:15,036 --> 01:47:17,470
[DoorOpens]

1209
01:47:54,742 --> 01:47:57,506
- [ Panting ]
- [Truck Passing]

1210
01:47:57,578 --> 01:48:00,103
Minute, five faster.

1211
01:48:01,949 --> 01:48:04,076
[ Chattering ]

1212
01:48:04,151 --> 01:48:06,881
See you in court.

1213
01:49:01,542 --> 01:49:04,807
[Boy Chattering]

1214
01:49:06,647 --> 01:49:10,447
[ Chattering ]

1215
01:49:42,163 --> 01:49:44,723
Captain Hanks has ordered you
to remain here, Chief.

1216
01:49:44,799 --> 01:49:48,860
[ Chattering ]

1217
01:49:53,842 --> 01:49:56,174
[Door Closes]

1218
01:50:11,526 --> 01:50:13,892
Please be seated,
Senior Chief Brashear.

1219
01:50:19,667 --> 01:50:23,103
Um, only the Army
salutes indoors, Senior Chief.

1220
01:50:23,171 --> 01:50:26,436
Sir, in the Navy I grew up in,
a salute is warranted...

1221
01:50:26,508 --> 01:50:29,068
given the gravity
of this occasion, sir.

1222
01:50:29,144 --> 01:50:32,272
Well... we're in a new Navy now,
Senior Chief.

1223
01:50:32,347 --> 01:50:35,316
[Crowd Murmuring]

1224
01:50:37,318 --> 01:50:40,082
[Hanks]
Shall we begin?

1225
01:50:41,256 --> 01:50:43,190
Senior Chief Brashear,

1226
01:50:43,258 --> 01:50:46,159
one day the life of another
diver may depend on you.

1227
01:50:46,227 --> 01:50:50,288
Do you honestly feel
that as a man--

1228
01:50:52,000 --> 01:50:55,731
You're almost 40.
You have one leg.

1229
01:50:55,804 --> 01:50:59,501
Can you really keep up with
healthy divers half your age?

1230
01:50:59,574 --> 01:51:04,136
The question is, sir,
can they keep up with me?

1231
01:51:04,212 --> 01:51:06,680
[Spectators Laughing]

1232
01:51:06,748 --> 01:51:09,182
- Bring the suit.
- Yes, sir.

1233
01:51:10,685 --> 01:51:13,017
No smoking
out here, Chief.

1234
01:51:21,629 --> 01:51:25,224
[Heavy Object Moving]

1235
01:51:25,300 --> 01:51:29,828
[Medical Officer]Studies of
the Navy's experimental diving unit...

1236
01:51:29,904 --> 01:51:34,170
indicate that if the subject
were to become unconscious...

1237
01:51:34,242 --> 01:51:38,474
or deceased, the disparity
between the buoyancy characteristics...

1238
01:51:38,546 --> 01:51:43,347
of a prosthetic and a limb
would hinder him in a free dive mode.

1239
01:51:43,418 --> 01:51:47,149
You mean if he drowned,
he wouldn't float right, yes?

1240
01:51:47,222 --> 01:51:50,191
- Yes, sir.
- Sir, I promise,

1241
01:51:50,258 --> 01:51:54,752
if I am killed at sea, I will make
every effort to die like a Navy man.

1242
01:51:54,829 --> 01:51:56,763
[Spectators Laughing]

1243
01:52:16,084 --> 01:52:19,053
[ Chattering ]

1244
01:52:20,822 --> 01:52:23,950
I just thought you should see
the future of Navy deep sea diving.

1245
01:52:24,025 --> 01:52:26,619
This is the latest HEO-2
mixed gas rig.

1246
01:52:26,694 --> 01:52:29,527
It weighs 290 pounds,
and the men who want to use it,

1247
01:52:29,597 --> 01:52:32,122
before they can even begin
the diving qualifications,

1248
01:52:32,200 --> 01:52:35,533
will be required to walk
12 steps, unassisted.

1249
01:52:37,839 --> 01:52:40,899
Could you do that,
Senior Chief Brashear?

1250
01:52:48,016 --> 01:52:50,382
Yes, sir, I could.

1251
01:52:50,451 --> 01:52:53,147
Well... I see.

1252
01:52:53,221 --> 01:52:56,384
As much as I hate
to prolong this another day,

1253
01:52:56,457 --> 01:52:58,448
I will, in the interests
of thoroughness,

1254
01:52:58,526 --> 01:53:01,086
make arrangements for you
to demonstrate your contention.

1255
01:53:01,162 --> 01:53:04,063
Here, sir. Now.

1256
01:53:04,132 --> 01:53:08,068
Son, step aside, or I'll have to
crack you right in the jaw.

1257
01:53:10,872 --> 01:53:13,841
[Hanks]Senior Chief Brashear,
I hardly think this is the appropriate--

1258
01:53:13,908 --> 01:53:19,244
- I want them all to see, sir.
- Captain Hanks, sir,
I concur with your assessment.

1259
01:53:19,314 --> 01:53:21,509
[Spectators Murmuring]

1260
01:53:23,384 --> 01:53:26,683
These slippery floors alone prohibit
such a demonstration, sir.

1261
01:53:26,754 --> 01:53:31,487
Chief Sunday, haven't you had
enough trouble in your career?
Your advice is unwelcome.

1262
01:53:31,559 --> 01:53:34,824
- Who is this man?
- Chief Leslie W. Sunday, sir.

1263
01:53:34,896 --> 01:53:39,424
You swam out of the Saint Lo
at Leyte Gulf.

1264
01:53:41,035 --> 01:53:44,664
You held your breath
for four minutes.

1265
01:53:44,739 --> 01:53:46,832
Five, sir.

1266
01:53:48,443 --> 01:53:50,434
[ Chuckles ]
He can stay.

1267
01:53:52,880 --> 01:53:55,940
[Hanks]
Fine. Irrelevant.

1268
01:53:56,017 --> 01:53:59,680
Gentlemen, sirs,
returning to the issue at hand.

1269
01:53:59,754 --> 01:54:03,815
This is not the time or place
for Senior Chief Brashear--

1270
01:54:05,960 --> 01:54:09,088
Excuse me, Senior Chief,
is there a problem?

1271
01:54:12,367 --> 01:54:18,237
Captain Hanks, I have spent most of my
life in the Navy trying only to succeed.

1272
01:54:18,306 --> 01:54:22,208
However, my questhas come at a great
personal loss to those who love me.

1273
01:54:22,277 --> 01:54:24,905
They, too,
have made sacrifices.

1274
01:54:24,979 --> 01:54:28,176
They, too, have endured
great pains to support me.

1275
01:54:28,249 --> 01:54:33,482
If I  walk these 12 steps today,
reinstate me to active duty.

1276
01:54:33,554 --> 01:54:35,579
Give me my career back.

1277
01:54:35,657 --> 01:54:39,753
Let me finish it
and go home in peace.

1278
01:54:42,330 --> 01:54:45,766
Senior Chief Brashear,
the business of the modern Navy--

1279
01:54:45,833 --> 01:54:49,860
Forgive me, sir. But to me,
the Navy is not a business.

1280
01:54:49,937 --> 01:54:53,873
We have many traditions. In my career,
I have experienced most of them.

1281
01:54:53,941 --> 01:54:56,535
Some good, some bad.

1282
01:54:56,611 --> 01:55:00,570
However, I wouldn't be here today
if it weren't for
our greatest tradition of all.

1283
01:55:00,648 --> 01:55:03,378
And which one is that?

1284
01:55:03,451 --> 01:55:06,181
Honor, sir.

1285
01:55:06,254 --> 01:55:08,722
[ Chuckles ]

1286
01:55:08,790 --> 01:55:11,725
[Spectators Murmuring]

1287
01:55:14,962 --> 01:55:17,863
Get on with it,
Senior Chief.

1288
01:55:20,535 --> 01:55:22,469
Leslie?

1289
01:55:24,205 --> 01:55:26,366
What leg you got on?

1290
01:55:26,441 --> 01:55:29,239
My walkin' leg, Leslie.

1291
01:55:29,310 --> 01:55:31,835
It was my dad's name.
You got a problem with that?

1292
01:55:31,913 --> 01:55:34,643
Oh, no.
No problem at all.

1293
01:55:40,455 --> 01:55:43,822
That thing's light duty.
Gonna snap like a match stick.

1294
01:55:43,891 --> 01:55:46,359
Not if I keep my weight
on my good leg.

1295
01:55:46,427 --> 01:55:50,488
Two hundred and ninety pounds
on one leg? You'll be
passed out by the sixth step.

1296
01:55:52,066 --> 01:55:55,035
Tenders, hat the diver.

1297
01:56:44,268 --> 01:56:46,259
Navy Diver, stand up.

1298
01:56:47,972 --> 01:56:50,099
Leave him.

1299
01:56:50,174 --> 01:56:53,701
Captain, if I recall the Navy
regulation manual correctly,

1300
01:56:53,777 --> 01:56:56,405
the diver
may be helped to his feet.

1301
01:56:56,480 --> 01:56:59,313
This is a lot of brass to sling up
from a seated position, sir.

1302
01:56:59,383 --> 01:57:03,251
It's spun copper, Chief.
We haven't used brass in a decade.

1303
01:57:03,320 --> 01:57:07,086
And the new manual states
the diver must rise unassisted.

1304
01:57:07,157 --> 01:57:10,752
That's what it says
in the new book, sir?

1305
01:57:10,828 --> 01:57:14,127
If I may ask, Captain,
how would you know?

1306
01:57:14,198 --> 01:57:15,961
I wrote it.

1307
01:57:16,033 --> 01:57:18,831
[Spectators Chuckling,
Murmuring]

1308
01:57:18,903 --> 01:57:20,894
Yes, sir.

1309
01:57:26,844 --> 01:57:29,506
Navy Diver, stand up.

1310
01:57:39,089 --> 01:57:42,183
Square that rig
and approach the rail.

1311
01:57:46,564 --> 01:57:49,294
[ Indistinct Whispering ]

1312
01:57:52,503 --> 01:57:54,733
[ Grunts, Gasps ]

1313
01:57:54,805 --> 01:57:56,966
[ Panting ]

1314
01:58:02,646 --> 01:58:04,170
One.

1315
01:58:06,283 --> 01:58:07,682
Two.

1316
01:58:10,321 --> 01:58:11,845
Three.

1317
01:58:11,922 --> 01:58:15,323
[ Panting Continues ]

1318
01:58:15,392 --> 01:58:16,882
Four.

1319
01:58:19,830 --> 01:58:21,263
Five.

1320
01:58:23,968 --> 01:58:25,367
Six.

1321
01:58:26,770 --> 01:58:28,067
Seven.

1322
01:58:29,607 --> 01:58:32,201
- [ Grunting ]
- Eight.

1323
01:58:32,276 --> 01:58:34,540
[Spectators Gasping,
Murmuring]

1324
01:58:37,915 --> 01:58:40,383
Gentlemen, his leg.

1325
01:58:40,451 --> 01:58:43,386
Please. Gentlemen.

1326
01:58:43,454 --> 01:58:45,854
[ Panting Continues ]

1327
01:58:45,923 --> 01:58:48,949
- Navy Diver, stand down.
- Diver, you will disregard.

1328
01:58:49,026 --> 01:58:51,859
- This is my detail.
- Admiral.

1329
01:58:51,929 --> 01:58:56,923
Goddamnit, cookie, move your ass!
I want my 12!

1330
01:59:05,442 --> 01:59:08,809
[ Whimpering ]

1331
01:59:08,879 --> 01:59:11,404
Nine. The Navy diver
is not a fighting man.

1332
01:59:11,482 --> 01:59:15,248
He is a salvage expert.
Ten.

1333
01:59:15,319 --> 01:59:18,914
If it's lost underwater, he finds it.
If it's sunk, he brings it up.

1334
01:59:18,989 --> 01:59:22,152
If it's in the way,
he moves it!

1335
01:59:22,226 --> 01:59:26,856
Eleven. If he's lucky, he will
die young 200 feet beneath the waves,

1336
01:59:26,930 --> 01:59:29,922
for that is the closest he will
ever get to being a hero!

1337
01:59:30,000 --> 01:59:33,333
Hell,I don't know why anybody
would want to be a Navy diver.

1338
01:59:33,404 --> 01:59:36,237
Now, you report
to this line, cookie!

1339
01:59:39,977 --> 01:59:43,003
At ease.

1340
01:59:43,080 --> 01:59:46,345
[Spectators Murmuring]

1341
01:59:53,824 --> 01:59:57,760
Tenders, unhat that diver.

1342
02:00:02,900 --> 02:00:05,528
[ Panting ]

1343
02:00:19,950 --> 02:00:23,113
The United States Navy
proudly reinstates...

1344
02:00:23,187 --> 02:00:27,317
Senior Chief and Diver
Carl Brashear...

1345
02:00:27,391 --> 02:00:30,224
to full, active duty.

1346
02:00:30,294 --> 02:00:34,230
[ Cheering ]

1347
02:00:36,800 --> 02:00:39,291
Thank you.

1348
02:00:47,745 --> 02:00:50,179
Congratulations, Captain.

1349
02:00:50,247 --> 02:00:52,374
Thank you.

1350
02:01:06,096 --> 02:01:07,996
I can quit.

1351
02:01:08,065 --> 02:01:11,660
The man I married never quit
anything a day in his life.

1352
02:01:16,707 --> 02:01:18,641
I love you.

1353
02:01:18,709 --> 02:01:23,009
I love you too, baby.
I love you too.

1354
02:01:38,829 --> 02:01:41,263
Well done, Chief.

